The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, February 02, 2004 				 I-T official in bribe net
																								New Delhi, Feb. 1 (PTI): The CBI has arrested a deputy director of income-tax and two others for allegedly taking a bribe from a man to settle his companys tax disputes.																								The three  Uma Shankar Dhyani, an Indian Revenue Service officer of the 1994 batch, chartered accountant Satya Prakash and his employee Ravi Verma  were produced before the duty magistrate, who sent them to CBI custody for two days, bureau sources said today. Dhyani conducted a survey on a company on January 20 and later allegedly demanded a bribe from its owner. 
